card.description: The Berger Action Fund is a nondescript name for a group with a rather specific purpose: steering the wealth of a Swiss billionaire, Hansj√∂rg Wyss, into the world of American politics and policy. As a foreign national, Wyss is prohibited from donating directly to candidates or political committees. But his influence is still broadly felt through millions of dollars routed through a network of nonprofit groups that have invested heavily liberal causes and candidates. Such groups don‚Äôt have to disclose the source of their funding ‚Äî or many details about how they spend it.
card.title: Group steers Swiss billionaire's money to liberal causes
